one phrasebook, pick up the hindi one as it will allow you to get by in most of india. while hindi is the main working language of the union government, and also commonly spoken as a second language by indians from outside the "hindi belt", it is by no means a lingua-franca for all of india. avoid speaking hindi in places such as tamil nadu and the northeast, as hindi is met with hostility from most of the locals there. also do not refer to the other languages as dialects of hindi; they are separate languages, mostly mutually unintelligible with 